Transluminal catheter angioplasty of abdominal aorta in Takayasu's arteritis. Nine patients with Takayasu's arteritis and a long stenotic segment of the abdominal aorta were treated by percutaneous transluminal angioplasty (PTA). Intermittent claudication disappeared in six of seven cases, the femoral pulse reappeared in all five ankle/arm indices increased in seven cases